SIMPLE: saccharinic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saccharinic
<hw>Sac"cha*rin"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or derived from, saccharin; specifically,
designating a complex acid not known in the free state but well known in
its salts, which are obtained by boiling dextrose and levulose (invert
sugar) with milk of lime.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saccharize</ent>⟦br⟧
